    <message>
      <heading>Mon Jul 23 (Jasurin)    :: &amp;gRequested Guildskills&amp;n</heading>
      <slot>12</slot>
      <level>203</level>
      <author>0</author>
      <date>0</date>
      <text>I have requested the following skills for the Ogier Guild.  They are
currently awaiting the HGL's approval, and then will be sumitted to the
coding staff for implementation...  someday.  Every guild member will
have at least 3 skills, 2 from their division and long stride.  Above
and beyond those, any guild member may eventually choose as many as four
more skills, up to the limit of 7 per character.  The ogier language will
not count toward that limit.

Treesinger Guildskills:

Treesing - target un-enhanced wooden item resists item damage, and gains &lt;3-5 hr/dr, and 5-10 ac/abs&gt; based upon current building values.  If equipment is ever rescaled, this skill ought to be as well.

Embrace Nature - This skill is like the spell 'sanctuary' which speeds up the heal rate, but this skill would of course only affect the user. Also, it would be more effective if the user was outdoors.

-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

Builder Guildskills:

Wall - as CotL 'fortify' skill.

Honor to the Builders - Ogier with this skill would experience a major reduction in cost at shops, and wouldn't be affected by human type aggro mobs.

-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

Soldier Guildskills:

Overbear - A character with this skill would automatically gain 50 abs during combat, and would additionally be able to use the command &quot;overbear &lt;target&gt;&quot;, which would operate as a damaging attack with a bash-like property, dealing approximately double attack damage, and preventing the target from attacking in the next round.

Slow Temper - An Ogier character with this skill, on first entering combat, would be set with a flag to represent his rising ire, much like a stormshield or sos, it would record reductions in his hitpoints, as well as elapsed time.  When it expired, either through damage or time, it would set a second affectation, which would give 1Xattack and heavy hr/dr bonuses.  After its expiration, the Ogier would begin again with the original counter, rebuilding to the full height of their temper...

-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

Scholar Guildskills:

Knowledge - (currently is coded, but not an Ogier gskill)

Naturalist - Using the consider command would reveal the target's maximum and current hitpoints, mana, and moves, as well as NPC flags...  perhaps in some sort of converted language?

-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

Miscellaneous Guildskills:

Long Stride - This skill would reduce the move cost between any two rooms to 1, cut all carting/taxi costs in half, and seriously increase the regeneration of movement points.

-&amp;gJasurin&amp;n
</text>
