    <message>
      <heading>Sun Sep 22 (Haran)      :: Re: Gaurav</heading>
      <slot>29</slot>
      <level>140</level>
      <author>0</author>
      <date>0</date>
      <text>Ok, so I'll lay down my crusade against the policy for the present.

However, I do have problems with syallabi and the Ogier.  I'm too lazy
to try to write this post out and reread it before posting, so bear with
me here.

1) My first thought immediately goes to lack of RP.  There are two main
factors in this.  1- There are hardly any active Ogier.  So you'll
suggest that I find RP outside of the Ogier, which brings about my second
problem. 2- Ogier almost never leave the Stedding and humans very rarely
enter them.  These two coupled together makes it very hard to get true
IC RP.  It can be circumvented, but its a rather meta-game way of thinking.

2) Ogiers, unlike humans, live incredibly long lifespans and therefore have
the opportunity to branch out in several directions of study.  Syllabi lock
people into a singular proffesion and a rigid caste like system.  Personally,
I don't even like the categories reflected in ranks.  Ogier often had great
masonry knowledge -and- a huge amount of knowlegde. 

Loial is the perfect example, pre-Rand.  He knew much about building, so
one could consider him as a builder.  However, he also had a fairly strong
ability to Treesing.  Next to that, he was insanely well-read and versed.
Now you'll probably say that using Loial as an example is like using Rand
as an example, but before he got involved, he lived a very normal Ogier life.

Ok, I've rambled enough. Syllabi bad.
-H-
