      <text>Haran,
&amp;n
You are correct that Ogiers have a life span that is staggering in comparison to their human counterparts.  However I think you are very wrong about Loial being anything but exceptional before he met Rand.    The two clues I see Jordan giving us that Loial is an exceptional person is 1. He devotes large chunks of the books to him (unlike Jarel a WC who is seen in one book for a few pages), and 2. He has a gift that is described as rare in the present day (treesinging).  Also Jordan does one thing we do not do here on Fang.  For every Ogier that is exceptional (Loial) he also gives us one that is unfortunate (Trayal, the Ogier who was a Treesinger but lost his minds in the ways). 
Now about your feeling that the average Ogier would know his history, building, and treesinging all together.  In a lot of ways I could not agree with you more.  Simple math tells us if the average human life span in RJs world is around 70 and the average Ogier lives to 600 dividing both by max ages by 3.8 (for the age of maturity) we find humans right at 18ish and Ogiers at 157ish years (although somewhere I think the books imply the Ogier age of maturity at around 100-120 but since I couldnt find it I just worked up a little thing).  So by the time an Ogier is at the age of maturity s/he could have legitimately read a bulk of masterpieces of the time, studied art, language, architecture, political science, pop culture, and restaurant management.  One the other hand does studying something give us the practical knowledge to use it or just an appreciation of the subject matter when it is used?  I would argue the latter, since I have B.F.A. in Theatre performance from a leading Theatre school in the US and spent time at another University in Canada studying under one of the most well know improve teachers of the 20th century, but I cant act for crap.  I have a great understanding of what goes into the craft of acting, yet I was simply not blessed with the inner light that shines through a truly gifted artist.
Role-playing options are not limited because of the Ogier race.  Instead RP options are limited because we are tying our hands behind our backs.  I will admit I do it with my major alt that is in the CotL.  I attempt only enter into RP when it meets my criteria for what I believe is good RP.  However how many times have I missed good RP because I was not willing to sit in a bar and partake in a little inn RP?  We will never know because it is missed.  One of our Ogier friends, Dalar found away to hold of the Longing for 10 years while he traveled with the SeaFolk (Mind you Dalar was Jordan's character and not subject to an anal GL :P).
Now, I too have rambled on far to long.  Perhaps anyone who is intrested can sit down under a tree with me to chat about this and other ideas that float past us on the clouds.
&amp;n
Regards,
Gauravs puppetmaster

</text>
